  "text": "Found 12 key files covering all aspects of CronJob API handling across v1beta1 and batch/v1:\n\n**Conversion functions**: `pkg/apis/batch/v1beta1/conversion.go` (field label conversions for v1beta1 CronJob), `pkg/apis/batch/v1/conversion.go` (field label conversions + manual JobSpec conversion functions needed due to v1beta1\u2192v1 dependency), and their auto-generated counterparts `zz_generated.conversion.go` in both version directories (containing CronJob/CronJobSpec/CronJobStatus conversion functions between versioned and internal types).\n\n**TimeZone field**: The `TimeZone *string` field is defined in the internal type (`pkg/apis/batch/types.go`), in the v1 external type (`staging/src/k8s.io/api/batch/v1/types.go`), and also in v1beta1 (`staging/src/k8s.io/api/batch/v1beta1/types.go`). All three carry it.\n\n**Validation**: `pkg/apis/batch/validation/validation.go` contains `ValidateCronJobCreate`, `ValidateCronJobUpdate`, `validateCronJobSpec` (which validates TimeZone via `validateTimeZone` and schedule format with timezone awareness), and the `validateTimeZone` helper.\n\n**Defaulting logic differences**: `pkg/apis/batch/v1beta1/defaults.go` sets CronJob defaults using raw pointer allocation (`new(bool)`, `new(int32)`), while `pkg/apis/batch/v1/defaults.go` uses `ptr.To()` helpers and additionally defaults Job-level fields. The `zz_generated.defaults.go` files in both version directories wire the defaulting functions into the scheme.",
